# Skills and Macs

## Macs first
Do the work on Adam's Macs via Tailscale / My Machines (`ssh studio` preferred). Do not claim you cannot access files, apps, builds, or signed-in sessions without trying his Macs first.

## Always-on behavior skills (vault)
Load and obey when relevant:
- `requirement-is-the-test` — Adam's literal sentence is the acceptance test; no "done" without evidence he can see
- `adams-words` — quote his rules verbatim; never paraphrase
- `no-time-estimates` — never estimate duration or urgency
- `cognitive-fit` — tables/lists over spatial metaphors
- `articulate-leadership-communication` — answer first, short; detail only if asked
- `market-inefficiency` — when deciding whether to build a product/feature from a spotted gap

## When stuck or broken
Use systematic debugging: reproduce → evidence → one hypothesis → fix. Do not spray random changes.

## When the same correction happens twice
Use `create-rule` / add a `.cursor/rules` entry so the class of mistake never repeats. Prefer system over one-off apology.
